                      </a>
      </div>
        <figcaption class="figure__info text-left font-serif text-xs md:text-sm lg:text-base mx-auto text-gray-700 mt-1"><span class="figure__caption">(Left): Stari Most, a 16th-century Ottoman-era bridge, in Mostar, Bosnia and Herzegovina, shown here in 1910. © 1910 József Plohn/Fortepan. (Right): In November 1993, Croat armed forces shelled and destroyed Stari Most over the Neretva River, in Mostar, Bosnia and Herzegovina.</span>
