<div id="ftn226">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a href="#_ftnref226" name="_ftn226" title="" id="_ftn226"><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span class="MsoFootnoteReference">[226]</span></span></a> For further discussion of this provision, see Human Rights Watch and IHRC, <i>Safeguarding Civilians: A Humanitarian Interpretation of the Political Declaration on the Use of Explosive Weapons in Populated Areas</i>, <span lang="EN" xml:lang="EN" xml:lang="EN">pp. 10-12. The purpose of the Declaration is evident in its preamble. </span><span lang="EN" xml:lang="EN" xml:lang="EN">The Oxford English Dictionary defines “refrain” as “to abstain from doing something.” The term is comparable to “avoid,” which the dictionary defines as "to have nothing to do with, refrain from.” “Restrict” is defined in the Oxford English Dictionary as “to confine to or within certain limits.” </span>Oxford English Dictionary Online, definition of “refrain” (verb) https://www.oed.com/dictionary/refrain_v (accessed October 23, 2023); Oxford English Dictionary Online, definition of “avoid” (verb), https://www.oed.com/dictionary/avoid_v (accessed October 2023, 2023); Oxford English Dictionary Online, definition of “restrict” (verb), https://www.oed.com/dictionary/restrict_v (accessed October 23, 2023).</p>
